          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Multi-sampling ionization chamber used as active",
                "target detector filled with CH4 as counting gas with",
                "carbon of the methane acting as a target. Gas",
                "pressure was asdjusted for different runs. At 65 MeV",
                "beam energy, the CH4 gas pressure was 154 Torr, A",
                "beam energy of 55 MeV, the gas pressure was 126 Torr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Multi-sampling ionization chamber (MUSIC) . The beam",
                "passed through a 2.11 mg/cm2 HAVAR window and a 3 cm",
                "dead layer of CH4 gas before entering the active",
                "volume of the detector. Chamber measures energy",
                "losses of the beam and the reaction products in a",
                "segmented anode. The anode is segmented into 18",
                "strips allowing for an energy loss measurement in 18",
                "different regions within the detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
